<TITLE> EPZs account for one-fifth of export earnings </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 14 (bdnews24.com) -- Export processing zones contribute 18 percent to the country's total export earnings, BEPZA executive chairman Ashraf Abdullah Yusuf said Wednesday. Yusuf made the disclosure in a statement after Myanmar deputy minister for commerce Aung Tun visited the Dhaka EPZ Tuesday. Bangladesh earned $12.1 billion from exports in fiscal 2006-07, according to the Export Promotion Bureau data. "We have set $2.5 billion as the earnings target from exports by the EPZs this fiscal year (2007-08," Ashraful Huq Khan, general manager of BEPZA, told bdnews24.com. EPZ export earnings were $1.8 billion in fiscal 2005-06. The Myanmar deputy minister had expressed satisfaction over the performance of the EPZs in export earnings as well as industrialisation in Bangladesh, Yusuf said. Aung Tun believed that economic activities of the EPZs would have a positive impact on the poverty alleviation initiatives. Currently, there are eight EPZs in Bangladesh where some two lakh people are directly employed. Currently, 264 enterprises are in operation in the EPZs. bd
